@Steelrat1994 No, Disney Star Wars can not be revived. As Disney Lucasfilm has shown with the High Republic era, they can not even do Star Wars separated from the mainline films right. 

And as much as you can counter with the relative competency of Andor, it is an exception to Disney Star War’s low quality rule that is also a pointless story whose very conflict is rendered moot with the goal of the Rebellion, the New Republic, being destroyed in The Force Awakens. Most of the characters die off to never be referenced again, much like Andor in Rogue One, and the plot meanders 30% of the time.

Product quality is not the only reason that Disney Star Wars’ audience has shrunk as with essentially every unpopular outing, the go-to response is to lash out at the audience. The only people left are basically abused housewives that have to wade through feces level content to search for a kernel of decent content, all the while being berated by the producer of said content. Disney Star Wars does not deserve a revival.

